        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2014-03-20 10:28:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Tests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.5/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/4714b33e-afff-11e3-9bc4-52540035b04c). Ran 4 tests. 2 tests failed: conf-sanity, sanity.\n\nBecause of OST_INDEX_LIST=[6-12], all of the sub-tests which directly use OST0000 or OST0001 failed. To make those tests passed, we need use facet_index() to get the real index of ost1 or ost2. However, this will involves many test script changes. I'll not add these changes in this patch, just revise the value of OST_INDEX_LIST instead.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
